sentences: Orrin James Olsen (born July 7, 1953) is a former American football center in the National Football League for the Kansas City Chiefs.
Olsen played one season with the Chiefs in 1976, which was notable because two of his brothers, Merlin and Phil, were also playing in the league at the time.
In 1975, his senior season, Olsen was again named first-team all-conference.
Since 1985, Olsen has worked for LDS Philanthropies as a Donor Liaison.
Olsen was a member of the Mormon Tabernacle Choir from 1973–74.
Olsen was selected by the Chiefs in the eighth round of the 1976 NFL draft.
An all-around athlete, Olsen was named All-American in football his senior year and set a state record in discus while competing on the track team.
His junior year, he was named pre-season All-American and first-team all-conference.
Olsen currently lives in Alpine, Utah.
